    <p>An intense, off-the-beaten-path expedition to the active stratovolcano revered by the Maasai as the &#39;Mountain of God.&#39; Rising sharply from the arid floor of the Rift Valley near Lake Natron, this challenging day trek is a steep, demanding ascent designed for adventurous climbers seeking raw volcanic geology and surreal landscapes.</p>
